CORTEZ OIL COMPANY v. Acel C. ALEXANDER, Collector. No. 524. Circuit Court of Appeals, Tenth Circuit. Jan. 11, 1932. Johnson & Shores, of New York City, for appellant. Herbert K. Hyde, U. S. Atty., of Oklahoma City, Old., for appellee.

Before LEWIS and COTTERAL, Circuit Judges, and KENNAMER, District Judge.

PER CURIAM.

Appeal dismissed on motion of appellant.
